Delete K-12 section for several reasons. Most importantly Prop 209 does not affect court-mandated desgreation program and was ruled in court to not block voluntary desegregation programs (https://www.sfgate.com/education/article/Berkeley-school-integration-challenge-rejected-3229308.php).  There's some relevant arguments here to justify prop 209, though ironically some require segregation to realize (more black teachers for black students) - I'll leave it to original author to restructure.

/* Public opinion regarding affirmative action */ Outcomes of push polls are not a reasonable way to judge "public opinion". It's also unclear from the sourced material that this series of questions (Q27-Q30) were actually asked to the same people in series.
Add counterpoint to Bleemer study to improve NPOV
